Sec. 78.002. LEGISLATIVE DETERMINATION. The legislature has
determined that:
(1) noxious weeds are present in this state to a degree
that poses a threat to agriculture and is deleterious to the proper
use of soil and other natural resources; and
(2) reclamation of land from noxious weeds is a public
right and duty in the interest of conservation and development of the
natural resources of the state.
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

